	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Nov 19th 12:40 AM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Using the experience breakdown given by Giddygonzalus, we can figure out about how many kills of black con mobs (or the average of blues, blacks, and yellows) you need to get to next level.&nbsp;&nbsp;Also, you can break it down to how many kills it takes of black cons for you to get 1 bub of exp.  Here is Halfling Druid for example levels 14-30 (Note the difference in kills for first hell level 30) (Also note these are approximates, hopefully I didn't use "fuzzy math")<br>(Referring to breakdown formula in previous post<br>I used this formula: (X*X*X*C*R*L/"black"MOB* "black"MOB*75)= kills per level.  Then divide by 6 (approximate)for each bubble.<br><br>Level       Kills per level     Kills per Bubble<br>14          180                 30<br>15          192                 32<br>16          204                 34<br>17          216                 36<br>18          228                 38<br>19          240                 40<br>20          252                 42<br>21          264                 44<br>22          276                 46<br>23          288                 48<br>24          300                 50<br>25          316                 53<br>26          329                 55<br>27          342                 57<br>28          353                 59<br>29          365                 61<br>30          418 (40 extra kills)70 <br><br>I think this works. Hope it is helpful info<br><br>Philo<br>14 level Halfling druid<br>7th hammer<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
	   </form></table><ul>

</ul>
