	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f97430395126305><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=8&mid=97430395126305>RE: Experience Breakdown</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=8&mid=97430395126305#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Nov 15th 10:59 AM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>This is really a great work!!<br><br>I did notice and agree on most of the points were given, they are accurate and sound, in a quantitative way, but if I haven't read wrongly, I think the exp gained in a group is not like that.<br><br>My druid hunted in Sol B at level 31 , grouping with 5 other 40ish players. I couldn't imagine, that the exp almost stopped! After I hunted 10 mobs, the exp move a drop, bah... all the mobs my group killed are con yellow or red to me. (mobs are all 33+) I would rather prefer solo in aviak city, hunting harrier or avocet, for every kill I made, my exp moved.<br><br>On the other case, I was level 44, again hunting in Sol B. In a same place of camp, once I hunted with players are similar level to me, all are 45ish, and once I hunted with players are a bit lower than me (40ish in average), this make good difference in exp gain after a couple of hours, the latter case gave me much better exp.<br><br>My conclusion is, the exp gained in group is proportionately shared among group members, which is related to their class/race penalty/bonus, and current level. When I grouped with most hybrid classes (high exp penalty), I could share less exp, therefore, I love grouping with warrior/rogue rather than SK, ranger, pally. Those hybrid classes slow my exp gained sharply.<br><br>Anyone has noticed this? Or it's just my wrong observation? And a further question, how does the factor L goes at post50? it seems very hard to level since level 51...<br><br>just my 2cp ^_^<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
