	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hmm, I am not sure what level mobs you are looking at, so I suppose the pp would have to be good for the mob's level, or you can do quests to make money.<br>You could get a partner and try doing the EE's in Beholder, so that you can get optic nerves and do the crafted bracer quest (costs about 105 pp to do, you can get a return of 10-45pp per bracer if they sell), or maybe some other quests.&nbsp;&nbsp;Crag spiders can be rewarding for their silks and poison sacs (in EK), but once again, it's debatable how much they will pay off.  Sometimes they drop a lot, sometimes they drop nothing.  <br>  Something you can also try is being a bank machine in high level zones like SK or Rathe Mountains.  People drop their copper or trade it in at good rates, so you could make a few pp there.<br>  I understand that aviaks are very rich mobs, so you could try killing them&gt; They give you xp and and up to a few pp.<br>Lastly, you could try Area effect dd's and shower spells to kill many mobs at once that are levels below you, like gnolls in EK.  Killing 5 at once could mean a few pp.<br>At 22 it's hard to find good ways to make money.  You may have to accept being broke until you can tp at 29.<br>Good luck :)<br>BTW, If your wis is somewhere past 150, I wouldn't worry to much about upgrading.  I would just level, beacause soon the money will roll in, or you can get the items yourself.  Sorry I couldn't be of more help.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
