	   <tr><td colspan=2>I can't remember exactly what I had at level 22, but here are some things to look for:<br><br>+6 wisdom rings (about 225pp each I think)<br>+3 wisdom earrings (cheap,less than 50pp/ I think)<br>Foreman's tunic- about 300pp (3 wis and 3 str, weighs 0)<br>Runed Circlet- 300-400pp: 4 ac 4 wis 4 int I think<br>Lizardscale mantle or Thistle's drop for the shoulders...each are a few hundred pp and give wis.&nbsp;&nbsp;The one from Thistle is better for wisdom. Gives 5 instead of 3 I believe<br>Gator legs- these are probably too expensive for a 22 druid, retailing at about 1kpp<br>Paw gloves- about 20pp, gives 2 wis and other stats<br>Get the Testament of Vanear, which is easy to complete after the mid-teens.  It's pretty cheap and no drop.  Forget about 2 handed weapons like the Staff of Observers, as they will be useless past about 30.<br>For the waist and feet, don't worry about getting wisdom items there until you are very high level.  Golden Efreeti boots and a reed belt are both about 15kpp<br>Anyhow, if you get even some of these items, your wisdom will be more than acceptable for your level.  If you are focusing on wisdom only, go for the 6 wis rings and work from there.  Don't forget that in dungeons ac will be important, so try to keep up your defence.  By the time you get 200 wisdom, you will probably not need it all and want to work on AC for those high level mobs.<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
