	   <a name=9726786129678></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9726786129678><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=8&mid=9726786129678>RE: whats the best class</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=8&mid=9726786129678#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Oct 27th 4:30 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I think that overall, halflings are the best druids, with woodelfs coming a close second.&nbsp;&nbsp;Wisdom is too important for druids, which is why I dismiss half elf and human druids.<br>Let's compare base stats:<br>            Halfling           Druid<br>Str            70                65<br>Sta            85                75  <br>Agi            95                95 <br>Dex            90                80<br>Wis            90                90<br>Int            67                75  <br>Char           50                75<br>points to add   30               30<br><br>Strength is important for offence, but also for CARRYING loot.  It's really annoying when you have to bank really often for being overweight.  The extra 5 makes a difference.  The stamina will give the halfling extra hp's, and the dex at lower levels will help them hit mobs a bit more.<br>The base wisdom is the same, but halflings will have less int.  I forget what that affects (learning or successfully casting spells and skills I think), but I prefer the extra stats that halflings get compared to what they lack.  Of course, charisma is mostly for selling stuff.  If you are a twink, it's not really a problem.  If you are starting from scratch, just be a bit more careful with your money,  You only have to buy food, water and spells from vendours for the most part.<br>All in all thought, the difference between halflings and woodelfs is considerably small.  If you play either, you won't be at a disadvantage.  I recommended maxing out on wis in char creation and putting remaining points into str and/or agi (for defence later on).  Even if you choose a human or half-elf druid, it won't be the end of the world.  Many druids of those races are high level too.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
