	   <tr><td colspan=2>OK, i have a lvl 28 druid on the e'ci server with wiz of 108, here is how i kite. 1)cast dmg shield on me (shield of barbs) 2)sight in mob and snare. 3)cast dot (swarm at lo lvls, Crud at 24) 3)then mana dump the careless lightning and dizzying wind until i have one bub of mana left (aprox 4to5 sucessfull casts. by this time the dot has worn off. 4)recast dot on mob and snare again (at this point im oom) usually by this time the mob has started running, but because of snare they dont move or attack,(dont root or they will still attack) 5) melee till it dies,usually the dot will finish it off. I REPEAT---ALL OF THIS IS DONE WITH A WIZ OF 108. most of the time i never get hit by mob at all. but cast the dmg shield just in case. I have been doing this since lvl 23 in lake of ill omen. Saranaks recruits and goblin warriors, these mobs have been droping 2 to 3 pp. I can easily solo by kiting for much more exp and loot than group hunting. Thats my take on kiting, If anyone who reads this is on E'ci my char name is Negluas, and i would be happy to demonstrate technique. HAVE FUN<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
