	   <tr><td colspan=2>hmm.. <br>I do agree its close, but I use the root/dot/run method.. it is very possible to put enough distance between you for just long enough to fire off another root. The people at Verant are infintely wise, because root has a REALLY long range. :) once you apply root, reapply the dot then keep running. the other thing you might want to do is root them first, apply the dot, then run about 200 feet (EQ feet) away and turn, basically watching them. Have them targeted, and the second they break root, recast.. they usually dont have enough time to close the gap before root gets cast again. Again, maximize on the distance you are able to cast root. You may want to practice in WC, kiting spiders or something, it may help you get the basics down. I know its a tough skill, and it is on flawless, it will fail sometimes.. I had a really hard time, being used to playing a mage... I keep thinking "WHEN DO DRUIDS GET PETS" :)Kiting is fun but it isnt the easiest thing to learn. practice practice practice. go to ec and kite the hell out of some hapless spiderling. :) its not about power or strenght, its all about tactics. hope this helps. <br><br>Nahualli<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
